{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"Fifth review BLOCK remediation:\n- Grounded ticket_store_revision in the existing tickets tracker git boundary: clean HEAD SHA after ensure_fresh; collection is bracketed by equal HEAD reads, then the same HEAD is verified under the global write lock before append+commit. Supported writes already commit under that lock, so mid-window writes change HEAD; dirty/unmerged state fails rather than compares.\n- Grounded old-reader compatibility: DSSE verifies the stored complete manifest list byte-for-byte, including unknown lines; older field parsers ignore unknown lines only after authentication and never reconstruct a filtered manifest.\n- Defined one ManifestFormatError contract for all new parsers and a single compute_validity catch point.\n- Added phase-compatibility ACs for claim, close, reuse, re-sign, audit, and health.\n- Co-located prerequisite Pass-2 attribution in the existing index-keyed schemas and specified deterministic size fallback using existing sizing helpers.\nRerunning epic review before any child review."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784523919812760001,"uuid":"edd7453b-d10e-427c-9c7b-c7e6fc3ba35e"}